description._content:
The Tees pilot boat, 'B.O. Davies' was built by William Gray & Co. Ltd. of Hartlepool. It was a cruising cutter and was launched on the 23rd April 1932. It was named after the Chairman of the Tees Pilotage Authority. It worked with the smaller cutter, 'W.R. Lister'. The 'B.O. Davies' was sold in 1955 and replaced by the 'Alderman B.O Davies' and 'W.W. Constantine'.
HAPMG : 1980.46.27
